- Are all HTTP methods acceptable? No. The method is explicitly mapped with method = RequestMethod.GET, so only GET is defined for this path.

- HEAD: Yes. In Spring MVC, HTTP HEAD requests are handled for GET-mapped endpoints by default (the framework can respond to HEAD using the same logic as GET, typically without a response body). - POST: No. Not mapped for this path.

- HEAD and OPTIONS are not explicitly declared in code, but Spring MVC provides appropriate default handling for these methods on GET-mapped endpoints (HEAD mirrors GET; OPTIONS reports allowed methods). Therefore, they are considered acceptable based on framework behavior.
- All other HTTP methods (POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE) are not defined for this path in the code, so they are not acceptable.
